You are building InternIQ — a once-in-a-generation SaaS for students to track internship applications, build stunning public portfolios, and leverage AI tools.
The design quality must exceed Linear, Stripe, Vercel, and Raycast tier polish.

## Immutable Design Commandments
1. Dark mode is the default. Use deep navy-charcoal backgrounds (never pure black).
2. Glass morphism is the UI language: blur, translucent layers, and subtle borders.
3. Every element animates with intentional choreography.
4. Accent colors glow: electric blue, purple, cyan. Colored shadows over black shadows.
5. Typography is dramatic and intentional with a strong hierarchy.
6. Interactions are magnetic: tilt cards, tactile press states, rich hover feedback.
7. Springs for motion: avoid linear easing for key transitions.

## Stack Requirements
- Next.js 14 App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind + shadcn/ui
- Framer Motion (+ LazyMotion/domAnimation where practical)
- @splinetool/react-spline, Lenis, @dnd-kit/core + sortable, Recharts
- next-themes, cmdk, Zustand, canvas-confetti, Sonner
- Supabase auth/database, FastAPI AI backend

## Implementation Guardrails
- Zero hardcoded color literals in product UI; use CSS variables/tokens.
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion for non-essential animation.
- Every new interactive component must support keyboard focus/visible ring.
- Mobile-first and fully responsive at 375 / 768 / 1280+.
- Avoid layout shifts (explicit dimensions and Suspense for dynamic content).

## Files and Architecture
- Marketing lives in `src/app/(marketing)`.
- Product dashboard lives in `src/app/(dashboard)/dashboard/*`.
- Shared motion presets live in `src/lib/animations.ts`.
- Kanban implementation uses dnd-kit + Zustand in `src/components/kanban` + `src/stores/kanban-store.ts`.
